                    "company": "Climate Vulnerable Forum (CVF) & Vulnerable Twenty Group (V20)",
                    "description": "Joined the CVF\u2019s newly launched Parliamentary Program where my role is to help unlock the full potential of parliaments and MPs from 58 climate vulnerable member states to advance climate actions globally. Also, to lend impetus driving legislative activities to reach the 1.5\u00b0C Paris Agreement goals, SDGs 2030 and Sendai Framework for disaster risk reduction and planetary prosperity through Climate Prosperity Plans. The CVF GPG Secretariat is led by a team of three staff, which has allowed me to pick up the craft of multitasking, producing high-quality documents in short time and meeting quick deadlines. \n\nMy roles are aimed at supporting CVF GPG lead events and realizing our key milestones to bring parliamentarians advocate for enhanced climate action. During events, my responsibilities include developing the concept notes, program and finalizing high level statements/talking points and briefing notes for parliamentary champions, drafting and issuing communique, outcome statements, press release, website post; logistic support in budget, procurement, outreach with CVF member states parliaments and capitals for quorum in meetings  communications with partners and social media engagement; active engagement with parliaments for enhanced advocacy. Currently preparing for the following upcoming events: \n- Preparing for 2nd CVF GPG Annual Dialogue at the 147th IPU General Assembly (Oct 2023) \n- Preparing for the CVF GPG Accountability Summit at COP28 (Nov 2023) \n\nCurrently, supporting the CVF GPG Research: \n\nCurrently conducting a legislative gaps analysis exercise for implementing the CVF Climate Prosperity Plans Legislative Plan of Action (Sri Lanka, Senegal, Maldives, Lebanon, Ghana, Benin and Bangladesh), which is a toolkit for parliamentarians to mainstream CPPs in vulnerable countries within the legislative functions of oversight, budget making, finance, representation and advocacy.",
